text_translated:
😬 Iran's new cardboard supreme leader made his first statement, but there is a nuance. Mojtaba Khamenei did not appear on camera, his speech was read out on television

— Khamenei confirmed the death of his wife and sister as a result of an attack by the United States and Israel and promised that he “will avenge the blood of the martyrs who died in this conflict”;

— Tehran should use the Strait of Hormuz as a lever in the conflict in the Middle East: “The Strait of Hormuz must remain closed”; 

— “We are committed to friendship with our neighbors and aim exclusively at the bases, and, if necessary, we will continue”;

— Called on Middle Eastern countries to close US bases in the region as soon as possible;

— Iran will demand compensation from the United States for damage caused as a result of the attacks.

